# Avenir Souriant — Internal Management Web App

Internal web app to centralize project management, student/staff tracking, scheduling, discussions, and governance for a Montréal-based Arabic language and cultural learning centre.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **You will need a database.** This app manages relational data (students enrolled in projects, staff assigned to sessions, approval workflows with audit logs, etc.). A flat file or localStorage approach would collapse under the complexity. PostgreSQL is recommended — it's free, robust, and handles relational data well.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Hosting decision needed.** The app needs to be hosted somewhere accessible by your staff. Options:
> - **Vercel + Supabase** (free tier, easiest to deploy, PostgreSQL included) ← Recommended
> - **Railway / Render** (cheap, simple, PostgreSQL included)
> - **Self-hosted** (your own server or VPS — more control, more maintenance)
>
> This affects how we configure the database and deployment. Please confirm your preference.

## Open Questions

1. **How many rooms** does the centre have? (Affects calendar seed data)
2. **How many committee members** typically review a project? (Affects the approval workflow — do all need to approve, or is majority sufficient?)
3. **Do you want email notifications** (e.g., when a project is submitted for review), or are in-app notifications sufficient for v1?
4. **Do you already have a domain name** for this app, or will you use a generated URL (e.g., `asc-admin.vercel.app`)?
5. **Do you want the initial admin account seeded automatically**, or do you want a setup wizard on first launch?

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Why |
|---|---|---|
| **Framework** | Next.js 15 (App Router) | Full-stack React — handles both UI and API routes in one project. No separate backend to maintain. |
| **Language** | TypeScript | Catches bugs early, great IDE support. |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL | Relational data (students → projects → sessions → rooms). Free tier on Supabase/Railway. |
| **ORM** | Prisma | Type-safe database queries, easy migrations, visual schema. |
| **Auth** | NextAuth.js (Auth.js v5) | Built-in session management, role-based access, credential-based login. |
| **Styling** | Vanilla CSS + CSS Modules | Clean, no extra dependencies. Print stylesheets are easy to control. |
| **Calendar** | Custom-built (CSS Grid) | The multi-room/filter requirements are specific enough that a library would fight us more than help. |
| **Icons** | Lucide React | Lightweight, consistent icon set. |
| **Deployment** | Vercel (pending your choice) | Zero-config for Next.js. |

> [!NOTE]
> This is intentionally **not** over-engineered. No Redux, no GraphQL, no microservices, no Docker. One Next.js project, one database, deployed to one place.

---

## Database Schema

```mermaid
erDiagram
    User {
        uuid id PK
        string name
        string email UK
        string passwordHash
        enum role "ADMIN | COMMITTEE | INSTRUCTOR"
        string phone
        jsonb availability
        timestamp createdAt
    }

    Project {
        uuid id PK
        string title
        text description
        enum type "WORKSHOP | COURSE | ACTIVITY"
        string targetAgeGroup
        string language
        enum status "DRAFT | SUBMITTED | UNDER_REVIEW | APPROVED | REJECTED | ACTIVE | COMPLETED | ARCHIVED"
        decimal registrationFee
        decimal projectedCosts
        decimal revenueEstimate
        decimal actualCosts
        decimal actualRevenue
        text publicDescription
        text promoNotes
        date enrollmentOpenDate
        date enrollmentCloseDate
        int maxCapacity
        uuid createdById FK
        timestamp createdAt
        timestamp updatedAt
    }

    ProjectStaff {
        uuid id PK
        uuid projectId FK
        uuid userId FK
        enum role "LEAD | CO_INSTRUCTOR | HELPER"
    }

    Session {
        uuid id PK
        uuid projectId FK
        uuid roomId FK
        datetime startTime
        datetime endTime
        boolean isCancelled
        text notes
    }

    Room {
        uuid id PK
        string name
        int capacity
        string color
    }

    Student {
        uuid id PK
        string firstName
        string lastName
        date dateOfBirth
        string parentName
        string parentEmail
        string parentPhone
        text notes
        text flags
        timestamp createdAt
    }

    Enrollment {
        uuid id PK
        uuid studentId FK
        uuid projectId FK
        enum status "CONFIRMED | WAITLIST | CANCELLED"
        timestamp enrolledAt
    }

    Attendance {
        uuid id PK
        uuid studentId FK
        uuid sessionId FK
        enum status "PRESENT | ABSENT | LATE | EXCUSED"
    }

    ReviewAction {
        uuid id PK
        uuid projectId FK
        uuid reviewerId FK
        enum action "APPROVE | REJECT | REQUEST_REVISION"
        text notes
        timestamp createdAt
    }

    Discussion {
        uuid id PK
        uuid projectId FK "nullable - null means general"
        string title
        timestamp createdAt
        uuid createdById FK
    }

    Message {
        uuid id PK
        uuid discussionId FK
        uuid authorId FK
        text content
        enum tag "QUESTION | FEEDBACK | DECISION | ACTION_ITEM"
        timestamp createdAt
    }

    Notification {
        uuid id PK
        uuid userId FK
        string title
        text content
        string link
        boolean isRead
        timestamp createdAt
    }

    User ||--o{ Project : "creates"
    User ||--o{ ProjectStaff : "assigned to"
    Project ||--o{ ProjectStaff : "has staff"
    Project ||--o{ Session : "has sessions"
    Room ||--o{ Session : "hosts"
    Student ||--o{ Enrollment : "enrolls"
    Project ||--o{ Enrollment : "has enrollments"
    Student ||--o{ Attendance : "attendance"
    Session ||--o{ Attendance : "tracks"
    Project ||--o{ ReviewAction : "reviewed"
    User ||--o{ ReviewAction : "reviews"
    Project ||--o{ Discussion : "has discussions"
    Discussion ||--o{ Message : "contains"
    User ||--o{ Message : "writes"
    User ||--o{ Notification : "receives"
```

