## UI/UX Design Principles

| Principle | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **French UI** | All labels, buttons, navigation, status badges, form fields in French. Data entered by users can be in any language. |
| **Clean & professional** | Muted color palette (navy, soft gray, white) with ASC brand accent. No visual clutter. |
| **Mobile-friendly** | Responsive sidebar → bottom nav on mobile. Tables become card lists on small screens. Calendar adapts to single-column on mobile. |
| **Non-technical staff** | Large click targets, clear labels, confirmation dialogs on destructive actions, inline help text on forms. |
| **Print-ready** | Dedicated `@media print` styles. Print buttons on calendar and schedule views. No sidebars/headers in print output. |

### Color Palette (Derived from ASC Branding)

| Token | Usage | Value |
|---|---|---|
| `--primary` | Buttons, active nav, links | Brand blue from ASC logo |
| `--primary-light` | Hover states, light backgrounds | Lighter variant |
| `--surface` | Cards, modals | `#ffffff` |
| `--background` | Page background | `#f5f6fa` |
| `--text` | Body text | `#1a1a2e` |
| `--text-muted` | Secondary text | `#6b7280` |
| `--success` | Approved, confirmed | `#059669` |
| `--warning` | Under review, waitlist | `#d97706` |
| `--danger` | Rejected, cancelled | `#dc2626` |
| `--border` | Dividers, input borders | `#e5e7eb` |

